('D9990', 'New York State Medicaid', 'billing_exclusion', 'Services provided by means of telehealth must be in compliance with the Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act (HIPAA) and all other relevant laws and regulations governing confidentiality, privacy, and consent (including, but not limited to 45 CFR Parts 160 and 164 [HIPAA Security Rules]; 42 CFR Part 2; PHL Article 27-F; and MHL Section 33.13). The acquisition, installation and maintenance of telecommunication devices or systems is not reimbursable. Place of Service (POS) code: Use 02, 10, or 11 on professional claims to specify the location teledentistry associated services were provided. Dental telehealth services shall adhere to the standards of appropriate patient care required in other dental health care settings, including but not limited to appropriate patient examination and review of the medical and dental history of the patient. Medicaid Update Archive • Attention Dentists: Billing Guidance for New York State Medicaid Members Who''ve Received a Pre-Paid Debit Card from Medicare Advantage Plans for Dental Services (Cover) – August 2025 • Attention: Federally Qualified Health Centers and Clinics Receiving a Prospective Payment System Rate or Threshold Payment for Dental Encounters – May 2025 • Topical Fluoride Application: Expansion of Provider Types – April 2025 • Dental Benefit Expansion of Criteria for Silver Diamine Fluoride – November 2024 • eConsults in the Dental Setting – October 2024 • Dental Panoramic and Periapical Radiographs Reimbursement Update for Medicaid Fee-for-Service Members and Medicaid Managed Care Enrollees – July 2024 • FFS Dental Claim Submission Guidance when Third Party Liability Payment Involved – May 2024 • Billing for Nitrous Oxide Analgesia, Anxiolysis, and Non-Intravenous Conscious Sedation in the Dental Setting – July 2023 • Billing for Dental Procedures in ASC Setting – July 2023 • Twenty Percent Increase in Reimbursement for Private Practitioners Treating the IDD Population – July 2023 • Reminder: Pre-Diagnostic Dental Procedure Codes in Dental Clinics Payable Under Ambulatory Patient Groups – August 2022 • New York State Medicaid Dental Services for Children in Foster Care Placement – June 2022 • Update to Dental Clinic Billing Logic in Ambulatory Patient Groups – December 2021 • Change to Dental Clinic Billing Logic in Ambulatory Patient Groups – July 2021 • Fluoride Varnish Application Expansion for ', 22.22, null, null, null, null, false, false, '{02,10}'::text[], '{81,95}'::text[], '{D1354,D9991,D9995,D9996,D9997}'::text[], 'XII. ADJUNCTIVE GENERAL SERVICES D9000-D9999', 67, '{"frequency_rule": null, "parser": "heuristic_v1", "source_slug": "nys_medicaid_dental_2026"}'::jsonb, (select id from src)),
